      <acqinfo id="aspace_fb5cca206e0fc09147ce79467e8fdb08">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The individual scripts were housed in the former Drama Library until their transfer to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library in 2008.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_75689c8f851f07a9fde54453cdc35c4f">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_cef115dea2ad5eb42f48ab614d91ba7d">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_4363f885fa36d590023e93d88ce6ba23">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Miscellaneous Scripts Collection, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_2f06c531c6989ad2b421638ef68a4b9c">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection consists of scripts written for the stage, screen, and television. It includes scripts from the "American Playhouse" PBS television series and the Federal Theatre Project.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_d92a803beca1b86e040457955c961b2e">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Plays. II. Screenplays. III. Teleplays.</p>
         <p>Arranged alphabetically by title within each series or subseries. More detailed inventory of contents available in repository.</p>  
      </arrangement>
